Directives : give instructions to Angular on how to render the templates to the DOM
  - Components
  - Structural Directives
  - Attribute Directives
can be defined as a class with a @Directive decorator

Structural Directives :
  allows the altering of the layout by adding ,removing or replacing elements in DOM
  examples :
      - *ngIf="object" => if object is defined the element is rendered into the dom
      - *ngFor = "let object of objects"
      - *ngSwitch
   Questions :
   how does angular detect changes and re-renders components
   whats the ngOnInit() function
